                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d429">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.77/136</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Chargé
                            <persName type="to">Scholle</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-08-31T13:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 31, 1916, 1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Request that Government of Haiti instruct Ménos to present immediately Haitian
                    Government’s statement in regard to National Railway Company, so that
                    conferences may be held next week. Now that gendarmerie protocol is signed
                    Department considers it advisable to bring to completion as soon as possible all
                    outstanding questions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
